 'Yes. You see, I don't know who the man was, but I gathered he was a difficult sort of man. She says she liked his looks and his hands and his manner of talking, and she thought it would be rather good fun to have him make love to her — because, you see, he looked so very intellectual, and it is always entertaining to see that kind of refined, distant — brainy fellow suddenly go on all fours and wag his tail What's the matter now, cher Monsieur?'



